elements.title: Jack the Ripper Stalks His Victims (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the clothing tags for Alexander McQueen's first collection, Jack the Ripper Stalks His Victims (garment pictured), had McQueen's own hair encased inside?

elements.title: Helene Ollendorff Curth (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Helene Ollendorff Curth was first to introduce a set of criteria for associating some rashes as possible indicators for internal cancers?

elements.title: Humayun Shah (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that according to a popular legend, the tomb of Humayun Shah split open when he was interred?

elements.title: channel 9 in Orlando, Florida (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the legal battle over awarding channel 9 in Orlando, Florida, the longest case in FCC history at the time, filled 55 volumes?

elements.title: Munich Mouser (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Munich Mouser, Neville Chamberlain's pet, and Nelson, Winston Churchill's pet, had a rivalry during World War II?

elements.title: Captain America (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that circulation numbers for early comic books featuring Captain America remained close to a million copies per month, outstripping news magazines such as Time?

elements.title: Blockchain Chicken Farm (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Blockchain Chicken Farm is about chicken farms run by people who have never heard of blockchain?
